UNITED STATES, Libelant-Appellant, v. Proceeds of the sale of THE GDANSK; Abram L. Burbank, Respondent-Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 14, 1924.) No. 192. William Hayward, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Herman L. Falk, of New York City, of counsel), for tbe United States. Louis Millsaps and C. P. Howland, both of New York City, for appellee.

Before ROGERS, MANTON, and MAYER, Gircuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed in open court.
